<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Compose" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Compose,</orth> 1) trans. a) to constitute, to form: <cit><quote>this --d wonder of your frame,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 59.10" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 59, 10</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>he's --d of harshness,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tmp 3.1.9" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. III, 1, 9</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. ado 5.1.257" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado V, 1, 257</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 1.1.48" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. I, 1, 48</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 1.2.21" default="NO" valid="yes">All's I, 2, 21</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 4.4.79" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. IV, 4, 79</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 5.2.170" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 2, 170</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 1.7.73" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. I, 7, 73</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 3.1.98" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. III, 1, 98</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 5.0" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. V Prol.</bibl> <bibl n="shak. per 5.0" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. V Prol.</bibl><lb />b) to make or write as a poet: <cit><quote>sonnets whose --d rhymes . . .</quote> <bibl n="shak. tgv 3.2.69" default="NO" valid="yes">Gentl. III, 2, 69</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. aww 3.7.40" default="NO" valid="yes">All's III, 7, 40</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 3.7.46" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 7, 46</bibl>.

<lb />2) intr. to come to a composition, to adjust differences: <cit><quote>if we c. well here, to Parthia,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ant 2.2.15" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. II, 2, 15</bibl></cit>.
